# set WT as the first -level -factor
# use raw readCounts with addition column - size factor
colData(DESeq.ds)$condition  <- relevel(colData(DESeq.ds)$condition , wtcondition)

# Run DESeq analysis
DESeq.ds <- DESeq(DESeq.ds)

# sequencing  depth  normalization between  the  samples
DESeq.ds <- estimateSizeFactors(DESeq.ds) 
# gene -wise  dispersion  estimates across  all  samples
DESeq.ds <- estimateDispersions(DESeq.ds) 
# this  fits a negative  binomial  GLM  and applies  Wald  statistics  to each  gene
DESeq.ds <- nbinomWaldTest(DESeq.ds) 

# Comment only for russians:

#тестовой статистике и т. д. для каждого гена.

DGE.results  <- results(DESeq.ds, independentFiltering = TRUE ,

# check or not

# edgeR.DGElist$samples

# summary(log2(rowSums(cpm(edgeR.DGElist))))
# remove  genes  that do not  have  one  count  per  million  in at  least 3 samples
keep  <- rowSums( cpm(edgeR.DGElist)  >= 1)  >= 3
edgeR.DGElist  <- edgeR.DGElist[keep ,]
# recompute  library  sizes  after  filtering
edgeR.DGElist$samples$lib.size  <- colSums(edgeR.DGElist$counts)
# head(edgeR.DGElist$samples)

# Count normalized factor (norm on LibrarySize)
edgeR.DGElist  <- calcNormFactors(edgeR.DGElist , method = "TMM")
# edgeR.DGElist$samples

# specify  the  design  setup - the  design  matrix  looks a bit  intimitating , but if
# you  just  focus on the  formula [~sample_info.edger] you can see  that it's
# exactly  what we used  for DESeq2 , too
design  <- model.matrix(~sample_info.edger)
# estimate  the  dispersion  for all  read  counts  across  all  samples
edgeR.DGElist  <- estimateDisp(edgeR.DGElist , design)
# fit the  negative  binomial  model
edger_fit  <- glmFit(edgeR.DGElist , design)
# perform  the  testing  for  every  gene  using  the neg. binomial  model 
edger_lrt  <- glmLRT(edger_fit)

# extract  results  from  edger_lrt$table  plus  adjusted p-values
DGE.results_edgeR  <- topTags(edger_lrt , n = Inf , # to  retrieve  all  genes
                              sort.by = "PValue", adjust.method = "BH")

DGE with limma !!!CAN BE SKIPPED!!!

# The little piece of theory:

# count values are transformed to log-cpm and instead of negative binomial models,
# linear models are used
# 1)  calculate the counts per million reads and log-transform thes
# 2)  Fit a linear model to the log-cpm values taking the experimental design into account (e.g., conditions,batches etc.
# 3) Use the resulting residual standard deviations for every gene to fit a global mean-variance trend acrossall genes and samples.
# 4) To obtain a “precision weight” forsinglegene observation
# # (i.e., for every sample!), the fitted log-cpmvalues from step 2 are used 
# to predict the counts for every gene and every sample. 
# The mean-variance trend  (step  3)  is  then  used  to  interpolate  the  
# corresponding  standard  deviation  for  these  predicted counts.
# # 5)The  squared  inverse  of  this  observation-wise  estimated  
# standard  deviation  is  used  as  a  penalty  (in-verse weight) during 
# the test for differential expression. 
# These penalty values are the above mentioned“precision weights”


# use  edgeR to  remove  lowly  expressed  genes  and  normalize  reads  for
#sequencing  depth; see  code  chunks  above
sample_info.edger  <- factor(c( rep(wtcondition, replics), rep(kocondition, replics)))
sample_info.edger  <- relevel(sample_info.edger , ref = wtcondition)
edgeR.DGElist  <- DGEList(counts = readcounts , group = sample_info.edger)
edgeR.DGElist$samples
##               group lib.size norm.factors
## WTNative_1 WTNative 31748545            1
## WTNative_2 WTNative 30623568            1
## WTNative_3 WTNative 37715313            1
## P1Native_1 P1Native 32561333            1
## P1Native_2 P1Native 34662903            1
## P1Native_3 P1Native 31776581            1
keep  <- rowSums( cpm(edgeR.DGElist) >= 1)  >= 3
edgeR.DGElist  <- edgeR.DGElist[keep ,]
edgeR.DGElist  <- calcNormFactors(edgeR.DGElist , method = "TMM")

# make design var for limma
design  <- model.matrix(~sample_info.edger)
rownames(design) <- colnames(edgeR.DGElist)

# transform  the  count  data to log2 -counts -per -million  and  estimate
# the mean -variance  relationship , which is used to  compute  weights
# for  each  count  -- this is  supposed  to make  the  read  counts
# amenable  to be used  with  linear  models
voomTransformed  <- voom(edgeR.DGElist , design , plot=TRUE)

# fit a linear  model  for  each  gene
voomed.fitted  <- lmFit(voomTransformed , design = design)

# compute  moderated t-statistics , moderated F-statistics ,
# and log -odds of  differential  expression
voomed.fitted  <- eBayes(voomed.fitted)

# extract  gene  list  with  logFC  and  statistical  measures
 # check  how  the  coefficient  is named
DGE.results_limma  <- topTable(voomed.fitted , 
                               coef = colnames(design)[2],
                               number = Inf , 
                               adjust.method = "BH",
                               sort.by = "logFC")

         species = "mmu", 
         limit = list(gene=5, cpd=1),
         out.suffix = paste0('_',
                             wtcondition,
                             '_vs_',
                             kocondition,
                             '_StemPath'))

# Extract genes info from pathview
path_genes <- pv_out$plot.data.gene[!is.na(pv_out$plot.data.gene$mol.data),]
if(nrow(path_genes) > 0){
path_and_genes_only <- data.frame(path_genes$labels, path_genes$all.mapped)
s <- strsplit(as.character(path_and_genes_only$path_genes.all.mapped), split = ",")
path_and_genes_only <- data.frame(V1 = rep(path_and_genes_only$path_genes.labels,
                                           sapply(s, length)), 
                                  V2 = unlist(s))
colnames(path_and_genes_only) <- c('Pathway', 'ENTREZID')
anno_f <- anno %>% filter(anno$ENTREZID %in% path_and_genes_only$ENTREZID)
anno_f <- anno_f[-6]
path_and_genes_only <- left_join(path_and_genes_only, anno_f[c(2,3,4)])

write.table(path_and_genes_only,file = paste0('mmu04550',
                                              '_',
                                              wtcondition,
                                              '_vs_',
                                              kocondition,
                                              '_StemPath',
                                              '.tsv'),
            sep = "\t", quote = FALSE , row.names = FALSE)
}
